<subSubSection id="5D851E06D6237F17FC7E2BD765370A8F" pageId="0" pageNumber="411" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="B6C0514AB10CA21DAF08352D2996129E" pageId="0" pageNumber="411">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A2C4BD1B5F1B38D08AFF7A824AD91F26" pageId="0" pageNumber="411">
This species occurs in numerous sites, both natural and agricultural. In natural sites, 
<bibRefCitation id="C92FC93F24337497F750E2759461D850" author="Plisko, JD" journalOrPublisher="African Invertebrates" pageId="0" pageNumber="411" pagination="323 - 334" refId="B45" refString="Plisko, JD, 2001. Notes on the occurrence of the introduced Pontoscolexcorethrurus (Mueller, 1857) in South Africa (Oligochaeta: Glossoscolecidae). African Invertebrates 42: 323 - 334" title="Notes on the occurrence of the introduced Pontoscolexcorethrurus (Mueller, 1857) in South Africa (Oligochaeta: Glossoscolecidae)." volume="42" year="2001">Plisko (2001)</bibRefCitation>
reported this species in grasslands, forests, natural bushes and near rivers. In cultivated fields, 
<taxonomicName id="16414D494ED00923266E73D771857F98" baseAuthorityName="Mueller" baseAuthorityYear="1857" class="Clitellata" family="Rhinodrilidae" genus="Pontoscolex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pontoscolex corenthrurus" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="0" pageNumber="411" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="corenthrurus">
<emphasis id="D08F187A9228DE52F6C400214FCFDC16" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="411">Pontoscolex corenthrurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been collected under most crops including maize, sugar-cane, banana, avocado, citrus; some specimens were collected in pine and gum plantations, some even from vegetable gardens (
<bibRefCitation id="69FB3E9B2B4A54C4579D132370FB26C1" author="Plisko, JD" journalOrPublisher="African Invertebrates" pageId="0" pageNumber="411" pagination="323 - 334" refId="B45" refString="Plisko, JD, 2001. Notes on the occurrence of the introduced Pontoscolexcorethrurus (Mueller, 1857) in South Africa (Oligochaeta: Glossoscolecidae). African Invertebrates 42: 323 - 334" title="Notes on the occurrence of the introduced Pontoscolexcorethrurus (Mueller, 1857) in South Africa (Oligochaeta: Glossoscolecidae)." volume="42" year="2001">Plisko 2001</bibRefCitation>
). This species has been used in experiments at different institutions. 
<taxonomicName id="FD9C435C882410002BF817B048CC14BF" baseAuthorityName="Mueller" baseAuthorityYear="1857" class="Clitellata" family="Rhinodrilidae" genus="Pontoscolex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pontoscolex corenthrurus" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="0" pageNumber="411" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="corenthrurus">
<emphasis id="6A962247FA2A989DFFCBD4869541C7C4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="411">Pontoscolex corenthrurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has also been collected in polluted sites in KZN (
<bibRefCitation id="AE1DC38D1F35EEBE8D5D24C74DEF72CC" author="Plisko, JD" journalOrPublisher="African Invertebrates" pageId="0" pageNumber="411" pagination="323 - 334" refId="B45" refString="Plisko, JD, 2001. Notes on the occurrence of the introduced Pontoscolexcorethrurus (Mueller, 1857) in South Africa (Oligochaeta: Glossoscolecidae). African Invertebrates 42: 323 - 334" title="Notes on the occurrence of the introduced Pontoscolexcorethrurus (Mueller, 1857) in South Africa (Oligochaeta: Glossoscolecidae)." volume="42" year="2001">Plisko 2001</bibRefCitation>
). The current collection was in sugarcane on one farm only, although we had expected to collect the species in other areas in the KZN Midlands because of its wide occurrence.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
